National Convention.

00:14.448 --> 00:20.354 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: It's day three,
and a star-studded
night on the main stage, with
speeches from

00:20.387 --> 00:26.326 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President Obama, Vice President
Joe Biden
and Hillary Clinton's running
mate, Tim Kaine.

00:26.360 --> 00:31.331 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Plus, part three of
our Hillary
Clinton biography series.

00:31.365 --> 00:36.870 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The first lady steps out from
the shadow of
her husband and into her own
political identity.

00:36.904 --> 00:41.308 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
INDIRA LAKSHMANAN, Journalist:
As soon as
she had a job to do and was a
Cabinet member

00:41.341 --> 00:46.046 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
