completely
relaxed and completely focused
on doing that

00:46.079 --> 00:47.314 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
job.

00:47.347 --> 00:49.149 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: And I'm Hari
Sreenivasan
in Washington.

00:49.182 --> 00:52.853 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
We will have all the
non-convention news of
the day, including the close of
the high-profile

00:52.886 --> 00:54.621 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Freddie Gray case.

00:54.655 --> 00:58.759 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A controversial death which
sparked national
protests ends with charges
dropped on three

00:58.792 --> 01:02.963 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
remaining officers involved, a
defeat for
the city's top prosecutor.

01:02.996 --> 01:11.004 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

01:11.038 --> 01:13.874 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:13.907 --> 01:24.084 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The Democratic
delegates here
in Philadelphia have now
completed their national

01:24.117 --> 01:25.886 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
ticket.

01:25.919 --> 01:30.290 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This afternoon, they voice-voted
the nomination
of Tim Kaine to be Hillary
Clinton's vice

01:30.324 --> 01:31.625 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
presidential running mate.

01:31.658 --> 01:33.860 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He will be a main speaker
tonight.

01:33.894 --> 01:38.765 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so will President Obama,
making the case
that his former secretary of
state is the

01:38.799 --> 01:43.203 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
nation's best hope of coming
together and
staying safe.

01:43.236 --> 01:45.272 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Correspondent John Yang begins
our coverage:

01:45.305 --> 01:50.711 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: At the White House,
President Obama
prepared for his last convention
as president.

01:50.744 --> 01:54.982 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
QUESTION: How do you feel about
tonight, Mr.
President?

01:55.015 --> 01:59.686 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA, President of the
United States:
What's happening tonight?

01:59.720 --> 02:00.754 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Oh.

02:00.787 --> 02:02.055 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
That was a joke.

02:02.089 --> 02:03.056 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You look so serious.

02:03.090 --> 02:04.891 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I feel great.

02:04.925 --> 02:06.493 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Also on the program
tonight, Vice
President Biden, and Hillary
Clinton's choice

02:06.526 --> 02:08.528 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to be the next vice president.

02:08.562 --> 02:12.032 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This morning, Virginia Senator
Tim Kaine spoke
to home state delegates.

02:12.065 --> 02:13.900 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

02:13.934 --> 02:16.169 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
TIM KAINE (D-VA), Vice
Presidential Candidate:
She's going to open up who we
are as a nation,

02:16.203 --> 02:18.271 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
who the leadership of this
nation is.

02:18.305 --> 02:21.775 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And people are going to be able
to see themselves
in that office who never could
have imagined

02:21.808 --> 02:23.577 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
it before.

02:23.610 --> 02:28.248 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think it's great for men to be
able to stand
and support strong women leaders
all across

02:28.281 --> 02:30.050 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
this nation.

02:30.083 --> 02:34.154 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JOHN YANG: Away from the
convention, more
fireworks over those hacked
Democratic National

02:34.187 --> 02:35.989 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Committee e-mails.

02:36.023 --> 02:40.694 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
American intelligence officials
say it appears
to be the work of the Russian
government.

02:40.727 --> 02:43.296 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Today, Donald Trump added fuel
to the fire.

02:43.330 --> 02:45.399 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP (R), Presidential
Candidate:
I will tell you this.

02:45.432 --> 02:54.141 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Russia, if you're listening, I
hope you're
able to find the 30,000 e-mails
that are missing.

02:54.174 --> 02:58.512 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think you will probably be
rewarded mightily
by our press.

02:58.545 --> 03:00.247 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Let's see if that happens.

03:00.280 --> 03:03.750 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: The Clinton campaign
said that
moved it from being a political
issue to a

03:03.784 --> 03:05.886 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
question of national security.

03:05.919 --> 03:11.258 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Back in Philadelphia, Bernie
Sanders urged
supporters to close ranks behind
the woman

03:11.291 --> 03:12.259 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
who defeated him.

03:12.292 --> 03:14.127 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

03:14.161 --> 03:15.729 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
BERNIE SANDERS (VT-I),
Presidential Candidate:
It is not good enough just to
elect Hillary

03:15.762 --> 03:17.597 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Clinton.

03:17.631 --> 03:23.470 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It is to transform America, and
to make sure
that we have a Democratic
Senate, a Democratic

03:23.503 --> 03:26.740 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
House and a Democratic president
who will
do that.

03:26.773 --> 03:28.375 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(APPLAUSE)

03:28.408 --> 03:30.877 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Last night, dozens of
Sanders delegates
walked out of the convention.

03:30.911 --> 03:32.979 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOMAN: We don't believe that
Clinton is a
true Democrat.

03:33.013 --> 03:35.315 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We don't think she really
believes in a true
democracy.

03:35.348 --> 03:39.152 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You count every vote, in every
state, and
you make sure they all have
every right to

03:39.186 --> 03:40.153 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
vote, in every single way.

03:40.187 --> 03:41.154 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
She doesn't care about that.

03:41.188 --> 03:43.423 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She has taken away our votes and
our voice.

03:43.457 --> 03:45.092 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We're making sure we're heard.

03:45.125 --> 03:49.729 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: In an interview with
NBC's "Today
Show," Mr. Obama called for
unity.

03:49.763 --> 03:58.705 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA: One of the dangers
in an election
like this is that people don't
take the challenge

03:58.738 --> 04:04.244 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
seriously, they stay home, and
we end up getting
the unexpected.

04:04.277 --> 04:08.482 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: A message he will
bring directly
to the delegates tonight.

04:08.515 --> 04:11.651 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm John
Yang in Philadelphia.

04:11.685 --> 04:18.091 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Next, we head down
to the convention
floor, where NPR's "Weekend
Edition Sunday"

04:18.125 --> 04:20.527 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
host, Rachel Martin, is standing
by.

04:20.560 --> 04:26.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Rachel joins us every night this
week as part
of our joint "PBS NewsHour" and
NPR convention

04:26.099 --> 04:27.067 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
coverage.

04:27.100 --> 04:28.068 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Rachel, what do we expect
tonight?

04:28.101 --> 04:30.036 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
RACHEL MARTIN: Hey, Gwen.

04:30.070 --> 04:32.806 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So the last couple of nights
here at the Democratic
National Convention have been
about healing

04:32.839 --> 04:35.542 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
those wounds caused in the
primary battle.

04:35.575 --> 04:37.611 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Tonight, Democrats are going to
try to turn
the page.

04:37.644 --> 04:42.716 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The focus is going to be on two
very important
issues, national security and
the economy.

04:42.749 --> 04:46.853 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Over the past couple of days,
Donald Trump
has really hammered the
Democrats, saying,

04:46.887 --> 04:48.355 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
where's the conversation about
ISIS?

04:48.388 --> 04:50.790 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Where's all the talk about the
threat from
terrorism?

04:50.824 --> 04:56.830 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Tonight will be the Democrats'
chance to answer
that and they will do it with
some heavy hitters,

04:56.863 --> 05:01.768 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
one of them, Leon Panetta, a
former director
of the CIA and former director
of defense.

05:01.801 --> 05:06.173 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He will take the stage and make
the case as
to why Hillary Clinton should be
the next

05:06.206 --> 05:07.974 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
commander in chief.

05:08.008 --> 05:12.179 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Also, on the economy, another
heavy hitter,
Vice President Joe Biden, he has
said that

05:12.212 --> 05:16.349 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Democrats have kind of forgotten
how to talk
to white working-class voters.

05:16.383 --> 05:19.653 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's going to reach directly out
to those
voters with his message tonight.

05:19.686 --> 05:25.125 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We will also hear from Tim
Kaine, Hillary
Clinton's vice presidential
pick.

05:25.158 --> 05:30.397 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, finally, closing out the
evening, the
keynote address will be from
Barack Obama,

05:30.430 --> 05:33.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
arguably Hillary Clinton's most
powerful surrogate.

05:33.233 --> 05:36.703 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
All eyes will be on him and his
message this
evening -- back to you.

05:36.736 --> 05:37.971 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Thank you,
Rachel.

05:38.004 --> 05:40.040 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We will be talking to you
throughout the night.

05:40.073 --> 05:44.711 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As we know, conventions are
often a place
where relative newcomers capture
the national

05:44.744 --> 05:46.146 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
political spotlight.

05:46.179 --> 05:51.151 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In 2012, that was true for
Julian Castro,
then mayor of San Antonio.

05:51.184 --> 05:56.089 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's now serving in President
Obama's Cabinet
as the secretary of housing and
urban development.

05:56.122 --> 06:01.695 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
His brother, Joaquin Castro, is
a second-term
congressman from San Antonio.

06:01.728 --> 06:06.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Both men are being floated as
potential next
heads of the Democratic National
Committee,

06:06.666 --> 06:08.201 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and both of them join us now.

06:08.235 --> 06:11.137 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we welcome you to the
program.

06:11.171 --> 06:13.206 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
To Julian Castro first.

06:13.240 --> 06:17.611 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You were -- I have to ask you,
you were clearly
on the list for Hillary Clinton
to consider

06:17.644 --> 06:19.579 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
as her vice presidential running
mate.

06:19.613 --> 06:21.014 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You even did a tryout.

06:21.047 --> 06:22.415 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You went out and campaigned with
her.

06:22.449 --> 06:24.184 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
She chose Tim Kaine.

06:24.217 --> 06:25.885 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Was he the best choice?

06:25.919 --> 06:26.920 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JULIAN CASTRO, U.S. Secretary of
Housing and
Urban Development: Oh, I think
he was.

06:26.953 --> 06:28.655 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
She chose an excellent man.

06:28.688 --> 06:30.590 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He's a very good man.

06:30.624 --> 06:34.227 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's very well-prepared, having
been a governor,
a senator, sitting on the Senate
Foreign Relations

06:34.261 --> 06:36.062 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Committee.

06:36.096 --> 06:42.168 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Maybe most importantly, he
shares a broad,
inclusive view of America, so he
is going

06:42.202 --> 06:46.673 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to be a great vice presidential
nominee and
a great vice president to serve
her.

06:46.706 --> 06:51.344 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Let's talk about the
great inclusive
role, Congressman Castro.

06:51.378 --> 06:56.716 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We know that Tim Kaine, among
other great
qualities, speaks Spanish quite
fluently.

06:56.750 --> 07:01.254 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, that brings me to the
question of what
two of the nation's leading
Latino politicians

07:01.288 --> 07:07.260 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
think about how this campaign is
playing out,
and whether Texas is in play and
whether Latino

07:07.294 --> 07:09.162 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
voters are in play for Donald
Trump?

07:09.195 --> 07:10.964 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

07:10.997 --> 07:12.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOAQUIN CASTRO (D), Texas: Well,
first, I
think that the Clinton campaign,
the Clinton-Kaine

07:12.699 --> 07:16.069 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
campaign now, is doing an
excellent job connecting
with Latino voters.

07:16.102 --> 07:20.640 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have seen more permanent
residents in this
cycle wanting to become
citizens.

07:20.674 --> 07:24.010 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have seen more people,
including many Hispanics,
registering to vote.

07:24.044 --> 07:25.912 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And so that's a good thing.

07:25.945 --> 07:31.551 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I do believe that she will
get upwards
of 75 percent of the Latino vote
in this election.

07:31.584 --> 07:36.923 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The fact is Donald Trump is
trying to divide
Americans along racial and
ethnic lines, and

07:36.956 --> 07:38.725 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
it's unhealthy for the country.

07:38.758 --> 07:43.196 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I say that as somebody who our
grandmother
came here from Mexico when she
was 6 years

07:43.229 --> 07:44.331 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
old.

07:44.364 --> 07:46.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And my grandmother was not a
murderer or a
rapist.

07:46.466 --> 07:48.968 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She was an orphan who came with
her younger
sister.

07:49.002 --> 07:55.542 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So to hear Donald Trump kick off
his campaign
with a slur against immigrants
was very hard

07:55.575 --> 07:57.644 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
to take.

07:57.677 --> 08:03.249 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JULIAN CASTRO: He really has,
truly has motivated
the Latino community more than
any other presidential

08:03.283 --> 08:07.053 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
candidate, I think, in
generations, and motivated
them in a negative way.

08:07.087 --> 08:13.326 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so if the turnout rate in
2012 among Hispanics
was 48 percent, I expect it to
go at least

08:13.360 --> 08:15.829 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
into the 50s for this election.

08:15.862 --> 08:20.900 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's going to, I think,
make a big difference
in places like Colorado, Nevada,
Florida,

08:20.934 --> 08:24.904 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
even in places like Virginia,
with Northern
Virginia, as diverse as it is.

08:24.938 --> 08:29.843 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
It was a mistake for the
Republicans to nominate
someone who is seen in the
Hispanic community

08:29.876 --> 08:31.611 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
as being against them.

08:31.644 --> 08:36.750 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: At the same time,
Congressman
Castro, you were quoted as
saying, I think,

08:36.783 --> 08:41.788 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
just a couple of days ago that
part of the
vote that Donald Trump is
attracting has to

08:41.821 --> 08:43.423 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
do with a fear about the
economy.

08:43.456 --> 08:44.424 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

08:44.457 --> 08:45.592 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JOAQUIN CASTRO: Sure.

08:45.625 --> 08:47.360 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Is Hillary
Clinton addressing
that?

08:47.394 --> 08:51.798 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I know Vice President Joe Biden
said in an
interview I think just today
that the party

08:51.831 --> 08:55.702 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
hasn't really spoken to those
Americans who
are worried about the economy.

08:55.735 --> 08:56.703 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

