49:10.648 --> 49:15.886 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And finally
tonight, we mark
the end of the primary season by
looking back

49:15.920 --> 49:20.558 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
at some of the iconic
photographs from the
2016 campaign so far.

49:20.591 --> 49:23.360 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we hear from the talented
men and women
who capture those images.

49:23.394 --> 49:27.064 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MELINA MARA, The Washington
Post: Covering
politicians is fascinating,
because they're

49:27.097 --> 49:28.899 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
almost like another breed.

49:28.933 --> 49:33.938 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As a political photojournalist,
my job isn't
only to document their message,
but it's also

49:33.971 --> 49:36.707 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to document the human being.

49:36.740 --> 49:38.042 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
My name is Melina Mara.

49:38.075 --> 49:41.145 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I'm the national political
photographer for
The Washington Post.

49:41.178 --> 49:46.517 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I have been on the campaign
trail with
Hillary Clinton for about a
year-and-a-half.

49:46.550 --> 49:50.187 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think she's very comfortable
with who she
is as a person.

49:50.221 --> 49:53.624 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I have a great time
photographing her, because
she's full of expression, she's
full of physicality.

49:53.657 --> 49:58.262 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHIP SOMODEVILLA, Getty Images:
I think just
photographing Trump is
fascinating.

49:58.295 --> 50:01.232 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He is such a character.

50:01.265 --> 50:02.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He's very conscious of the
camera.

50:02.566 --> 50:07.171 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He loves the camera, and it
comes across in
his pictures.

50:07.204 --> 50:08.973 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
My name is Chip Somodevilla.

50:09.006 --> 50:12.877 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And I have been a staff
photographer for Getty
Images in Washington, D.C., for
11 years.

50:12.910 --> 50:18.749 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This campaign cycle blended in
immediately
from the last campaign cycle, so
we have been

50:18.782 --> 50:22.086 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
covering this campaign the last
four years,
more or less.

50:22.119 --> 50:25.189 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JIM BOURG, Reuters News
Pictures: In my experience
in over 30 years of doing this,
there has

50:25.222 --> 50:27.691 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
